* Investigate\nMemory Spill
** What is Spill
***_ Memory insufficient
***_ Intermediate data → disk
***_ Significantly slows jobs
***_ During shuffle/aggregation
** Identify in Spark UI
***_ Stage page
***_ Shuffle Spill (Memory)
***_ Shuffle Spill (Disk)
***_ Any non-zero = memory pressure
** Resolve: Increase Partitions
***_ Reduce data per partition
***_ Set to "auto"
***_ spark.sql.shuffle.partitions
** Resolve: Add Memory
***_ Higher memory:core ratio
***_ More worker nodes
** Resolve: Optimize Data
***_ Select only needed columns
***_ Filter early in pipeline
***_ Less data per stage
** Skew and Spill
***_ Often occur together
***_ Fix skew → spill resolves
@endmindmap
